Enum GhostMovementAlgorithmType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<GhostMovementAlgorithmType>
      • edu.sjsu.cs.ghost151.GhostMovementAlgorithmType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<GhostMovementAlgorithmType>

    public enum GhostMovementAlgorithmType
extends java.lang.Enum<GhostMovementAlgorithmType>
    The GhostMovementAlgorithmType is an enumeration factory for creating appropriate instances of the GhostMovementAlgorithm interface. There are three algorithms defined:
    • RANDOM: The ghost chooses a random unexplored position and moves towards it
    • LINEAR: The ghost scans linearly outward in all 8 directions from its current position and moves towards the nearest unexplored space
    • NEAREST: The ghost moves towards the nearest unexplored space
